702422f-a.title: Brooklyn: 5th Street (South) - Wythe Avenue
702422f-a.text:
59-73 South 5th Street, north side, from and including Wythe Ave.,
to but not including Berry Street. Also seen is 365-373 Wythe Ave.,
east side, at, adjoining and north of South 5th Street. The buildings
ahown are frame.
April 11, 1931.
P. L. Snerr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

707468f-b.title: Brooklyn: Wythe Ave. - 5th St. S.
707468f-b.text:
Wythe Ave., east side, north from South 5th Street. This view from
the Williamsburg Bridge, shows in the foreground, parallel with the bridge, 1
a group of frame houses that are to be demolished.
October 19, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

is David Weil LithogmapkicCo.Building. In the center of the view is
seen P.S. No. 37, degicting an old type of school architecture.
September 1, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
